Judul: THREE DEMENSIONAL ELASTODYNAMICS AND FRACTURE MECHANICS SIMULATIONS USING SMOOTHED PARTICLE HYDRODYNAMICS
Abstrak:
Smooth particle hydrodynamics (SPH) is a Lagrangian based and meshless
method which can be applied in several field such as astrophysics, fluid
mechanics, and solid mechanics. The idea of SPH is calculate the properties
of discrete particles in the support domain using smoothing function. The
smoothing function determine the effect of neighbouring particles which are
interact to each other. In this project, SPH is applied to simulate three dimensional
problem in elastodynamics and fracture mechanics.
